<h2 id="first-tune-to-double-drop-d">First, tune to double-drop D</h2>

<p>That means your thickest string and thinnest string (both â€œEâ€ in standard tuning) will need to be tuned one whole step down to a â€œDâ€.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Standard tuning      = E A D G B E
Double Drop D tuning = D A D G B D
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>A good way to make sure youâ€™re all tuned up and ready is to rock a D-major chord in double-drop D. It should sound nice and full, given 3 of the 6 strings are tuned to the same note.</p>

